<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>FAQs - Short.ly</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background-color: #f8f9fa;
      padding: 30px;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: auto;
      background: #fff;
      padding: 20px 30px;
      box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
      border-radius: 8px;
    }

    h1 {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
      color: #343a40;
    }

    .faq {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .faq h3 {
      color: #007bff;
    }

    .faq p {
      margin-top: 5px;
      color: #333;
    }

    a {
      color: #007bff;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>1. What is a Short.ly?</h3>
      <p>A Short.ly is a tool that converts a long web address into a shorter, easy-to-share version.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>2. Is this Short.ly free to use?</h3>
      <p>Yes, our service is completely free for all users.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>3. How long does the shortened link stay active?</h3>
      <p>By default, shortened links do not expire. However, we may remove inactive links after a long period of time.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>4. Can I track how many times my short URL has been used?</h3>
      <p>This feature is coming soon. Stay tuned!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>5. Can I delete a shortened URL?</h3>
      <p>Currently, users cannot delete shortened URLs manually. Please <a href="/contactus">contact us</a> for support.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>6. Is there a limit to how many URLs I can shorten?</h3>
      <p>No, there is no strict limit. However, excessive abuse may lead to rate-limiting.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>7. Are my links private?</h3>
      <p>Shortened links are public by nature. Avoid shortening URLs that contain private or sensitive information.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>8. Where can I report a broken or malicious link?</h3>
      <p>Please report such links through our <a href="/contactus">Contact Us</a> page.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
